        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> I posted this idea here a couple of weeks ago</P><P>would be an awesome spell for us to have and would make necros a great addition to raids.  </P><P>To the person who said this is just like twitching... wtf?  How is it anything like twitching.  Just because its a spell that helps someone else and not ourselves?  It would be no different to healing or buffing in that sense.</P><P>Lets face it we probably arent ever going to be useful on raids simply for our damage.  They would have to fix dot stacking, give us more unresistable dots and drastically decrease the aggro of our dots for us to compete with wizards</P><P>There are only a few things we are useful for in a raid atm, twitching/mindwrack, summoning corpses, DMF on rare occassions and maybe resing a cleric after a wipeout if you have an EE.  </P><P>Classes which are needed for raids are useful mainly for specialised utility skills.  Tanking, buffing, healing, slow, tash, malo, COH etc.  twitching and summoning corpses and DMF is all we have in this area, if we want to be useful we need more of these kind of spells.  Dot damage and pets will be a nice bonus but not the only thing we are good for.</P><P>There is nothing intrinsic about being a necro that means we cant get useful buffs or other spells etc.  Group taps are a nice example, but still not good enough, if the taps affected the whole raid then that would rock.</P><P>How about an immune to fear buff, what about a skele illusion spell which would be useful in places where shrink doesnt work for ogres etc, and perhaps give some extra AC also.  Or maybe the ability to cast lich on a group member.  A lvl 60 version of scent line which is unresistable.  The ability to cast harmshield on a group member.</P><P>Basically what we should want on a raid is to be useful so that without a necro the raid would be severly hampered or a failure and the knowledge that you did somethin which saved the raid force or enabled the raid force to kill the mob.</P><P></P><P> </font></td>
