      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Alaaraaf</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>To the person who said this is just like twitching... wtf?  How is it anything like twitching.  Just because its a spell that helps someone else and not ourselves?  It would be no different to healing or buffing in that sense.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>I suspect this is compared to twitching, because the Necromancer gets screwed by it.  If a raid is getting wiped and you've dropped FD on a Cleric, is it likely that you're going to get FD off on yourself, before you die?  It seems unlikely.</P><P>This would, of course, be a different matter if you were talking about a group FD!</P><P>The complaint with twitching, seems to be that rather than being given something useful to do, a twitching Necromancer is merely allowing someone else to do something useful.  Plus, between the lousy transfer ratio, the long recast time, mod rods and various mana regen spells, it's not even all that useful!</P><P>There're a coupla other potential problems:<BR><ul><li>FD someone at the wrong time.  Someone yells to FD the Clerics and you drop him, just before a CH goes off.  <i>(I'm not a raiding person.  I just don't have the time.  But how long is the time delay between it becoming clear the raid is going pear shaped and everyone dying?)</i></li><BR><li>Occupying another precious spell slot!  Personally, I could do with several dozen more spell slots.  But, ya just have to make do with whatcha got, dontcha.  Do you wanna give up one of your slots for this?</li><BR><li>FD just isn't all that reliable.  Despite seeing other Necromancers complain about this, until <b>very</b> recently, I was fortunate enough not to be badly effected.  However, having suffered several deaths very recently, due to failed FD's, I'm beginning to see the point.  Once you factor in AEs, which screw up FD and seem to be a staple of most raid mobs <b>and</b> the new caster AI which has created a number of nasty chain casters, it's probably not actually that useful.</li><BR><li>Is there anything much a Cleric can do in the event of a re-aggro, after he gets up?  A Necromancer, trying to start a res cycle, has Harmshield, QVox, FD, Invis and Skins to draw upon to stay alive.  Can a Cleric seriously hope to fend off even a minor threat?  <i>(I'm guessing not, but I genuinely don't know.)</i></li></ul></P><P>Anywho...</P><P>AlAaraaf.</P><P><BR> </font></td>
