 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Takilth SP</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Sally - good point on the cleric.  In that case the only way you'd want to use a FD like this is if it always succeeded and you weren't dealing with AoE mobs.  That's not such a problem though when you think about it.  Consider it a limitation that prevents the skill from being overpowering.  However, let's think outside the box.  Why not FD a PC when they are low health and getting beat on to provide time for a heal to come in?  The fact is, it's not a tool that will be the bandaid for everything - I never suggested that.  Would it be another cool addition to our toolkit?  Would we be able to find good uses for it?  Sure.</P><P>Regarding the raid issue - I agree that there are already lots of things that we can do.  If you're a good player and know your character, you can do a lot.  But this is about moving forward - considering spells/skills that could be added that would be entertaining, useful, and in character.  Why NOT have another toy in our bag of tricks?</P><P></P><P> </font></td>
